theorem Topology.interior_compl_eq_compl_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) = (closure (A : Set X))ᶜ := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately and then apply `Subset.antisymm`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- First inclusion: `interior (Aᶜ) ⊆ (closure A)ᶜ`.
    intro x hx
    -- Suppose, for a contradiction, that `x ∈ closure A`.
    by_cases h_in : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X)
    · -- Show that this leads to a contradiction with `hx`.
      have h_nonempty :
          ((interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ)) ∩ (A : Set X) : Set X).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff).1 h_in _ isOpen_interior hx
      -- But the two sets are disjoint, since
      -- `interior (Aᶜ)` is contained in `Aᶜ`.
      have h_disjoint :
          ((interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ)) ∩ (A : Set X) : Set X) = ∅ := by
        apply Set.eq_empty_iff_forall_not_mem.mpr
        intro y hy
        have : (y : X) ∈ (A : Set X)ᶜ :=
          (interior_subset :
            interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ) hy.1
        exact this hy.2
      have : False := by
        simpa [h_disjoint] using h_nonempty
      exact this.elim
    · -- If `x ∉ closure A`, then `x ∈ (closure A)ᶜ`, as desired.
      exact h_in
  · -- Second inclusion: `(closure A)ᶜ ⊆ interior (Aᶜ)`.
    -- The set `(closure A)ᶜ` is open and contained in `Aᶜ`,
    -- hence lies in the interior of `Aᶜ`.
    have h_open : IsOpen ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) :=
      (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X))).isOpen_compl
    have h_subset :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X)ᶜ := by
      -- Taking complements of the inclusion `A ⊆ closure A`.
      simpa using
        Set.compl_subset_compl.mpr (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
    -- Apply `interior_maximal`.
    intro x hx
    have h_interior :
        ((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ interior ((A : Set X)ᶜ) :=
      interior_maximal h_subset h_open
    exact h_interior hx

theorem Topology.compl_closure_inter_self_nonempty_iff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    (((closure (A : Set X))ᶜ) ∩ A : Set X).Nonempty ↔ False := by
  constructor
  · intro hne
    rcases hne with ⟨x, ⟨hx_not_cl, hxA⟩⟩
    have : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hxA
    exact hx_not_cl this
  · intro hFalse
    cases hFalse
